    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but some people say the renewables-only approach is basically a fantasy because of the intermittency issues and the massive land use needed. if we actually want to stop the damage happening right now, shouldn't we just be prioritizing nuclear instead of wasting time on stuff that might not work at scale?",
